on, Walter (August 16, 2016). "Gary Johnson and the Rise of Libertarian Centrism". Reason.com. Retrieved September 7, 2016. ^ "audioBoom / 8-23-16: Curtis talks with Libertarian Presidential Candidate Gary Johnson, the latest on Clinton Pay for Play, Steve Levy, and Black Lives Matters Hunt the Clan in Long Island". Audioboom.com. August 23, 2016. Retrieved August 23, 2016. ^ Tucker, Jeffrey A. (May 30, 2016). "The GOP Implosion and the Rebirth of (Classical) Liberalism | Foundation for Economic Education". Fee.org. Retrieved July 24, 2016. ^ "Noted Third Party Advocate Richard Winger Endorses Gov. Gary Johnson for President". garyjohnson2016.com. April 20, 2016. Archived from the original on April 25, 2016. Retrieved May 13, 2016. ^ "Editorial: Vote Johnson | Editorial". caledonianrecord.com. August 9, 2016. Retrieved September 14, 2016. ^ Board, Editorial. "A principled option for U.S. president: Endorsing Gary Johnson, Libertarian". ^ Board, The Editorial. "We support Johnson for president". ^ "Endorsement: Libertarian Gary Johnson for president". ^ "Union Leader of New Hampshire Endorses Gary Johnson Over Donald Trump". The New York Times. September 15, 2016. ^ "A liberating presidential-vote solution". ^ "Richmond Times-Dispatch endorses Gary Johnson for president". Richmond Times-Dispatch. Retrieved September 3, 2016. ^ "Decision 2016: Gary Johnson for president". Winston-Salem Journal. September 11, 2016. Retrieved September 11, 2016. ^ "Our pick: Elect Gary Johnson for president". ^ Keller, Phoebe (September 3, 2016). "N.Y. Federation of College Republicans Revokes Recognition of Cornell Chapter Following Johnson Endorsement". The Cornell Daily Sun. Retrieved September 4, 2016. ^ Richard Winger, Independence Party of New York Nominates Gary Johnson for President, Ballot Access News (September 9, 2016). ^ MPP Marijuana Policy [@MarijuanaPolicy] (June 10, 2016). "MPP officially endorses @LPNational A+ candidate @GovGaryJohnson !" (Tweet). Retrieved July 16, 20